2026-03-21 16:01:53 [DEBUG   ] generation.llm - LLM response (2546 chars):
Bhai, judiciary ke baare mein kuch interesting facts suno:  

### 1. **"Fastest Justice" in History**  
   - 1959 mein, Supreme Court ne **9 minutes** mein ek case decide kiya! **KM Nanavati vs State of Maharashtra** (Bollywood movie *"Rustom"* ka real-life case) pe hearing hui aur same day judgment aa gaya. Aajkal toh 9 saal bhi lag jaate hain! [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 1]  

### 2. **Sabse Old High Court – Calcutta**  
   - India ka sabse purana High Court **1862** mein Calcutta (ab Kolkata) mein bana. British raj ke zamane ka hai! Allahabad High Court sabse bada hai, jisme **160 judges** ka strength hai. [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 3]  

### 3. **Pehla Jury Trial – 1665 mein!**  
   - India ka pehla jury trial **Madras (Chennai)** mein hua tha, jahan ek British aurat (Ascentia Dawes) ko uske slave girl ko maarne ka case suna gaya. Jury ne use **"Not Guilty"** kar diya! [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 6]  

### 4. **Supreme Court Judges ka Retirement Age – 65**  
   - High Court judges retire at **62**, but Supreme Court judges ko **3 saal extra** milta hai (65 tak). Par High Court judges ko promote karke Supreme Court mein bhej diya toh unka retirement age badh jaata hai! [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 1]  

### 5. **Lok Adalats – Free & Fast Justice**  
   - Lok Adalats ne **crores of cases** settle kiye hain, especially traffic challans, bank disputes, aur family matters. Ye **free** hai, aur decision final hota hai – appeal nahi hoti! [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Pages 4, 6]  

### 6. **Judges ki "7 Deadly Sins"**  
   - Ex-Supreme Court judge **Justice Ruma Pal** ne judiciary ki 7 bad habits batayi:  
     1. Corruption cover-up  
     2. Hypocrisy  
     3. Secret appointments  
     4. Copy-paste judgments  
     5. Arrogance  
     6. Lazy homework  
     7. Nepotism (Bhai-bhatijawaad)  
     [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 5]  

### 7. **E-Courts – Online Justice**  
   - Ab cases ki status check karne ke liye **http://lobis.nic.in** pe ja sakte ho! Video conferencing se witnesses bhi aa sakte hain. Par abhi bhi taluk level tak poori tarah implement nahi hua. [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 6]  

### 8. **466 Saal Ka Pending Case Load!**  
   - Delhi High Court ke paas itne pending cases hain ki agar har case **5 minutes** mein decide ho, tab bhi sab clear karne mein **466 saal** lagenge! [Source: judiciary-of-india.pdf, Page 4]  

**TL;DR:** Indian judiciary mein drama, delay, aur dhamakedaar cases ka full paisa vasool entertainment hai! 😆
